        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be <2% for hemolysis index QoI at all five VAD operating points. Richardson extrapolation must be applied on at least three grids with refinement ratio ≥1.3."
      },
      "rationale": "GCI computed via Richardson extrapolation across coarse (4.2M), medium (11.8M), and fine (31.4M) cell grids. GCI for hemolysis index ranged 0.3–1.1% across all five operating points, well within the 2% threshold. Asymptotic convergence ratio confirmed at 0.98."
