        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must be the primary QoI and must be directly linked to the clinical hemolysis threshold specified in the device submission. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, exposure time distributions) must be documented."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH selected as primary QoI per ASTM F1841 and ISO 10993-4. NIH directly maps to the clinical threshold of <0.01 g/100L. Secondary QoIs (volume-averaged shear stress, Lagrangian exposure time) documented in QoI specification QS-COU2-2025."
    },
    {
