      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Turbulence model selection must be justified by comparison of at least two turbulence models against PIV data. Hemolysis power-law model must be justified by published validation data for the shear-stress and exposure-time ranges present in the COU."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-ω and realizable k-ε models compared against PIV velocity data; SST k-ω selected based on superior near-wall velocity prediction (MAE 7.4% vs 12.1%). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model validated for shear stresses 1–400 Pa and exposure times 1–700 ms, covering 97% of the computational domain. Justification documented in MF-COU2-2025."
    },
    {
