        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/model-inputs",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "All uncertain model inputs (fluid viscosity, hemolysis model coefficients, inlet velocity profile) must be characterized with probability distributions and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ with ≥1000 samples. Input uncertainty must be traceable to measurement data or published literature."
      },
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 2500 Latin hypercube samples. Uncertain inputs: dynamic viscosity (N(0.0035, 0.0002) Pa·s), hemolysis coefficient α (N(3.62e-7, 4.1e-8)), power-law exponent β (N(2.416, 0.072)), inlet velocity profile (5% turbulence intensity uncertainty). All distributions traceable to published sources. Results archived in UQ-COU2-MC-2025."
