        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Hemolysis experiments must use at least three independent blood samples per operating point. Sample-to-sample variability must be quantified and reported as part of experimental uncertainty."
      },
      "rationale": "Hemolysis bench tests conducted with five independent porcine blood draws per operating point (n=25 total). Inter-sample coefficient of variation ranged 4.2–8.7% across operating points. Sample variability incorporated into experimental uncertainty bounds reported in TR-COU2-EXP-2025."
    },
